The emperor's new clothes is a story by Hans Christian Anderson about two weavers who promise

92
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:36,159
an emperor a new suit of clothes that is invisible to those who are stupid or incompetent.

93
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:42,080
No one dares to say that he doesn't see any suit of clothes and sort of child cries out,

94
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,920
but he isn't wearing anything at all.

95
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:46,800
It's a great story and a lesson to us all.

96
00:05:47,439 --> 00:05:49,840
